@namespace TheCanalaveLibrary.Client
@using TheCanalaveLibrary.SharedUI

@* Global Flip (layer5-wasm.md §"The Global Flip" step 1): moved Server→Client so the Router can
   run inside the WASM runtime — the WASM pass of InteractiveAuto cannot execute a component that
   lives in the Server assembly. Assembly targeting changed with the move:
   - AppAssembly = SharedUI (every routable page lives there);
   - AdditionalAssemblies = this Client assembly;
   - the Server assembly is deliberately ABSENT: WASM can't load it, and its routable components
     (Identity pages, /Error) are exactly the ones that must stay static SSR — a URL the
     interactive router can't match falls back to a full-document navigation, which server-side
     endpoint discovery (MapRazorComponents<App> + AddAdditionalAssemblies in Program.cs) then
     serves. That fallback IS the Identity-page escape hatch, replacing the old reliance on
     [ExcludeFromInteractiveRouting] metadata being visible to the router. *@
<Router AppAssembly="typeof(SharedUIAssemblyIdentifier).Assembly"
        AdditionalAssemblies="new[] { typeof(WasmClientAssemblyIdentifier).Assembly }"
        NotFoundPage="typeof(NotFound)">
    <Found Context="routeData">
        <CascadingAuthenticationState>
            <ThemeContextProvider>
                <ReaderDisplayProvider>
                    <UserActivityTracker />
                    <AuthorizeRouteView RouteData="routeData" DefaultLayout="typeof(DeviceLayout)" />
                </ReaderDisplayProvider>
            </ThemeContextProvider>
        </CascadingAuthenticationState>
        <FocusOnNavigate RouteData="routeData" Selector="h1"/>
    </Found>
</Router>
